overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser testing of a sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent systematically navigated and tested
  various aspects, including the questionnaire's multi-section flow, form
  validation, PDF report generation, and admin login functionality. During
  testing, the agent encountered and debugged navigation issues, eventually
  confirming the core functionality. It also verified API endpoints for data
  submission, PDF generation, and CSV export, noting that admin endpoints
  required authentication. After completing the testing, the agent provided a
  detailed summary of its findings, highlighting both working features and minor
  issues like ESLint warnings and an incorrect page title. Subsequently, the
  agent addressed these issues by updating the page title and committing a
  series of related feature enhancements to the questionnaire, report, PDF, and
  CSV export, following conventional commit guidelines.
